# =============================================================================
# TrussC addon .gitignore (addon root)
# =============================================================================
# Scope: addon-level + repo-wide concerns only. Each example/ is a normal
# TrussC project and carries its OWN standard .gitignore (the projectGenerator
# template), so that an example can be copied out and used as a starting
# project unchanged. That per-example .gitignore handles the project's
# generated files — CMakeLists.txt, CMakePresets.json, build dirs, bin/ — so
# we deliberately do NOT manage example internals from here.
#
# Note the asymmetry:
#   - example CMakeLists.txt  → generated by trusscli, ignored (not committed)
#   - the addon's OWN root CMakeLists.txt (optional custom build) → COMMITTED,
#     so it is intentionally absent from this ignore list.

# FetchContent / vendored deps (only when a root CMakeLists.txt fetches them)
libs/

# IDE / editor
.vscode/
.vs/
.idea/
.cache/
.clangd/
.ccls-cache/

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Secrets — never commit these (defensive; harmless if unused)
.env
.env.*
secrets.json
secrets.*
*.local

# AI assistant scratch / auto-generated instructions.
# Ignored by default; delete a line if you deliberately commit a curated file.
CLAUDE.md
GEMINI.md
.cursor/
.cursorrules
.aider*
.claude/
.gemini/
.github/copilot-instructions.md
